{
  "id": 5196629995028480,
  "name": "Respect autocorrect=\"off\" for Windows touch keyboard in TSF",
  "summary": "The HTML autocorrect attribute allows web authors to control whether autocorrection should be applied to user input in editable elements including <input>, <textarea>, and contenteditable hosts. On Windows, the touch keyboard ignores this attribute and always autocorrects words. For example, typing \"truf\" followed by space in an element with autocorrect=\"off\" yields \"true \" instead of preserving \"truf \". This feature makes Chrome's TSF integration detect and revert touch keyboard autocorrections when the focused editable element has autocorrect=\"off\" set.",
